    pearls: ["Breslow depth is the single most important prognostic factor -- measured in mm from the granular layer to the deepest tumor cell; determines excision margins, need for SLNB, and staging","Never perform a shave biopsy on a suspected melanoma -- it may transect the base and prevent accurate Breslow depth measurement; excisional biopsy with narrow margins is the standard","ABCDE criteria for melanoma screening: Asymmetry, Border irregularity, Color variation, Diameter >6mm, Evolving -- but amelanotic melanomas lack pigmentation and require high clinical suspicion","BRAF V600E mutation is present in approximately 50% of cutaneous melanomas and is required for targeted therapy eligibility -- always send for molecular testing","Sentinel lymph node biopsy is recommended for melanomas >0.8mm Breslow depth or any depth with ulceration; a positive SLNB upstages the disease and changes adjuvant treatment decisions","Immune checkpoint inhibitors (anti-PD-1) are first-line adjuvant therapy for stage III melanoma; monitor for immune-related adverse events at every visit -- thyroid dysfunction is the most common endocrine irAE","The 'ugly duckling' sign -- a mole that looks different from the patient's other moles -- is a clinically useful screening tool that complements ABCDE criteria"],
