        rationale: "Dexamethasone must be administered BEFORE or simultaneously with the first antibiotic dose to provide benefit. If antibiotics have already been given >1 hour prior, the inflammatory cascade has already been triggered by bacterial lysis, and dexamethasone will not provide its protective benefit against inflammation-mediated neuronal damage."
