        correct: 1,
        rationale: "Waterhouse-Friderichsen syndrome is bilateral adrenal hemorrhagic necrosis causing acute adrenal insufficiency. It presents with refractory hypotension despite fluids, bilateral flank pain, and critically low cortisol levels. This is a devastating complication of meningococcemia requiring immediate stress-dose hydrocortisone (100mg IV)."
