        correct: 1,
        rationale: "Close contacts of meningococcal disease require chemoprophylaxis within 24 hours. Ciprofloxacin 500mg PO single dose is the simplest effective regimen for adult contacts. Alternatives include rifampin 600mg PO q12h for 2 days or ceftriaxone 250mg IM single dose. The other antibiotics listed are not effective for meningococcal chemoprophylaxis."
