    pearls: ["The luteal phase is consistently ~14 days regardless of cycle length — cycle length variability is due to follicular phase duration; this is why 'day 21 progesterone' is only accurate for 28-day cycles (for a 35-day cycle, check progesterone on day 28)","GnRH must be secreted in a PULSATILE pattern for normal gonadotropin release — continuous GnRH administration paradoxically SUPPRESSES FSH/LH (this is the pharmacologic basis of GnRH agonist therapy)","The progesterone withdrawal test is a key diagnostic tool: withdrawal bleeding = adequate estrogen + patent outflow tract; no bleeding = hypoestrogenism or anatomic obstruction (next: estrogen-progestogen challenge)","PCOS diagnosis requires 2 of 3 Rotterdam criteria: oligo/anovulation, clinical/biochemical hyperandrogenism, polycystic ovarian morphology on ultrasound — AND exclusion of other etiologies","In hypothalamic amenorrhea, FSH and LH are both LOW (hypogonadotropic hypogonadism) because the problem is inadequate GnRH stimulation — this distinguishes it from primary ovarian insufficiency where FSH is HIGH (hypergonadotropic hypogonadism)","Unopposed estrogen (anovulatory cycles without progesterone opposition) increases endometrial cancer risk — all anovulatory patients need either cyclic progesterone or combined hormonal contraceptives for endometrial protection"],
